---
import CaseStudyLayout from "../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro";

const meta = [
  { label: "Year", value: "2023" },
  { label: "Client", value: "Close Brothers" },
  { label: "Role", value: "Lead Product Designer" },
  { label: "Timeline", value: "18 months" },
];

const stats = [
  { value: "400k+", label: "Containers in fleet" },
  { value: "150+", label: "Breweries onboarded" },
  { value: "100", label: "Sign-ups in 6 weeks" },
  { value: "95%", label: "Needed no training" },
];
---

<CaseStudyLayout
  pageTitle="Ekeg+ — Sammy Norris"
  caseNumber="02"
  lede="Pay-per-fill kegs, tracked in real time."
  meta={meta}
  description="Ekeg+ gives breweries of any size on-demand access to over 400,000 kegs and casks, tracked in real time and billed only when in use — removing the upfront costs and logistical burden of managing their own fleet."
  signoff="Designed at Close Brothers"
  signoffYear="2023"
>
  <Fragment slot="title">Ekeg<em>+</em></Fragment>

  <!-- Figure 01 — hero shot, two angled phones -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/ekeg/image-ekeg-1-m.jpg" />
      <img src="/images/projects/ekeg/image-ekeg-1.jpg" alt="Container enquiry detail screen on phone" loading="eager" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Chapter I — Challenge -->
  <section class="chapter" data-reveal>
    <header class="chapter__head">
      <span class="chapter__num">I.</span>
      <span class="chapter__label b2">The challenge</span>
    </header>

    <blockquote class="chapter__quote">
      Over seven million kegs and casks circulate across the UK brewing
      industry. For breweries, managing that fleet means high upfront costs,
      manual stock checking, and a constant battle to keep pace with
      fluctuating demand.
    </blockquote>

    <div class="chapter__body">
      <p class="b1">
        Ekeg+ is a pay-per-fill container rental platform that removes the
        financial and logistical barriers to running a keg fleet. Breweries
        rent from a pool of over 400,000 containers, paying only for the time
        they're in use. RFID tracking and a management platform let brewers
        scan and locate hundreds of containers in seconds, replacing
        unreliable manual stock checks with real-time data on rental cycles,
        usage, and billing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Figure 02 — bento collage with hand-held phone -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/ekeg/image-ekeg-2-m.jpg" />
      <img src="/images/projects/ekeg/image-ekeg-2.jpg" alt="Scan, fill and location flows for managing kegs" loading="lazy" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Chapter II — Process -->
  <section class="chapter" data-reveal>
    <header class="chapter__head">
      <span class="chapter__num">II.</span>
      <span class="chapter__label b2">The process</span>
    </header>

    <h2 class="chapter__h2">
      Eighteen months <em>embedded in the work.</em>
    </h2>

    <div class="chapter__body chapter__body--double">
      <p class="b1">
        As lead designer, embedded in the delivery team for eighteen months,
        the work was structured around an iterative discovery and design
        process built on continuous user insight. That meant interviewing
        brewers, shadowing front-office teams, observing training calls, and
        feeding qualitative and quantitative feedback directly into the
        backlog.
      </p>
      <p class="b1">
        The platform serves a wide range of users — master brewers, delivery
        drivers, production managers, finance admins — so accessibility and
        simplicity weren't optional. New features emerged directly from
        research, including a Help Mode for new users and keg-fill warnings
        to prevent production interruptions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Figure 03 — features bento with plusportal -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/ekeg/image-ekeg-3-m.jpg" />
      <img src="/images/projects/ekeg/image-ekeg-3.jpg" alt="Feature overview and plusportal companion product" loading="lazy" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Chapter III — Outcome -->
  <section class="chapter" data-reveal>
    <header class="chapter__head">
      <span class="chapter__num">III.</span>
      <span class="chapter__label b2">The outcome</span>
    </header>

    <h2 class="chapter__h2">
      150+ breweries. <em>No training required.</em>
    </h2>

    <div class="stats">
      {stats.map((s) => (
        <div class="stat">
          <span class="stat__value">{s.value}</span>
          <span class="stat__label b3">{s.label}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="chapter__body chapter__body--double">
      <p class="b1">
        Over 100 customers signed up in the first six weeks. Self-serve
        onboarding and a simplified interface meant 95% of brewers needed no
        training at all. Today the platform is used by more than 150
        breweries and growing.
      </p>
      <p class="b1">
        Beyond the commercial outcomes, Ekeg+ has a tangible sustainability
        angle — reducing surplus containers, minimising shipping through
        combined delivery and collection runs, and giving breweries access to
        a modern cleaning facility that uses significantly less acid and
        bleach than traditional alternatives. The project was nominated for a
        UX Design Award, recognised for its user-centred approach to solving
        a genuinely complex operational problem for an industry under
        pressure.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Figure 04 — fill flow, three phones -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/ekeg/image-ekeg-4-m.jpg" />
      <img src="/images/projects/ekeg/image-ekeg-4.jpg" alt="Fill flow across three screens" loading="lazy" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Figure 05 — login + brew assignment, three phones -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/ekeg/image-ekeg-5-m.jpg" />
      <img src="/images/projects/ekeg/image-ekeg-5.jpg" alt="Login with Ekeg+ card and brew assignment screens" loading="lazy" />
    </picture>
  </figure>
</CaseStudyLayout>
